name: "Moody Bastard" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Liner pen on notebook with EXTREME digital embellishment, color, and moshing!] He never likes to stand still for a portrait, but this moody bastard just made history. He became the heir to the IzzitBacon Co. fortune (the longest existing faux-bacon manufacturing company in all of New Jersey!) Sorry to intrude, Mr. Bastard, but you're NEWS now! ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
